fr.sorbonne_u.cps.smartcity.grid

Class AbsolutePosition

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sorbonne_u.cps.smartcity.grid.AbsolutePosition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    IntersectionPosition

    public class AbsolutePosition
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    The class AbsolutePosition implements a position in the smart city.

    Description

    Positions are defined by coordinates in a grid of streets and avenues crossing at 90 degrees. As position are meant to be either on streets or avenues, at least one of the coordinate must be integral to be on a street or on an avenue.

    Invariant

     invariant       AbsolutePosition.inGrid(getX())
 invariant       AbsolutePosition.inGrid(getY())
 invariant       AbsolutePosition.onGrid(getX()) || AbsolutePosition.onGrid(getY())

    Created on : 2021-12-23

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant
